It is a project where I document the step-by-step process of making a dockerized image for java applications.

Below are useful Java compile commands:

a) Create a java file with main class like in below format,

# vi HelloWorld.java

public class HelloWorld {
    public static void main(String args[]){
        System.out.println("Hello World!");
    }
}

b) Generate class file using javac command

# javac HelloWorld.java

c) Create MANIFEST.MF file contains like this,
Manifest-Version: 1.0
Created-By: Me
Main-Class: HelloWorld

d) jar cfm HelloWorld.jar MANIFEST.MF HelloWorld.class

e) Check if everything works correctly, type

# java -jar HelloWorld.jar



